Durban - KZN police have confirmed that the man linked to the disappearance of Miguel Louw lived a few metres away from where a body was found on Monday afternoon. 
 

 The 43-year-old charged with human trafficking was granted R2500 bail on Wednesday in the Durban Magistrate's Court but could not come up with the money, KZN police said. 

 

 He remains behind bars at Westville Prison. 

 

 KZN police spokesperson Thembeka Mbele said the identity of the deceased could not be confirmed at this stage, however a few of Miguel's relatives are on scene. 

 

 
  







