   KZN police spokesperson Colonel Thembeka Mbele. Video: Chanelle Lutchman.
  
 

 She said investigations would begin on Tuesday and that Miguel's family would be allowed to identify the body. 

 

 She said the body, which was found with school clothes, was at an advanced stage of decomposition. 

 

 The mortuary van has since left the scene. 
 Police are also leaving the scene. 

 

 People from the community have also started dispersing and were earlier
  seen taking photographs and videos from the scene. 

 

